edu.umd.cs.psl.model.argument

Interface UniqueID

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<GroundTerm>, GroundTerm, Term
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    RDBMSUniqueIntID, RDBMSUniqueStringID

    public interface UniqueID
extends GroundTerm
    A unique identifier for a distinct entity.

    DataStores and Databases use UniqueIDs to identify distinct entities for performance reasons. They should be used instead of Attributes when the GroundTerm is expected to appear in multiple GroundAtoms.

    For example, people in a social network should probably be represented as UniqueIDs, but their properties, such as names or ages, should probably be Attributes.

    See Also:
    DataStore.getUniqueID(Object), Database.getUniqueID(Object)
